{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784616900740", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "严重发现：同作者此前已有一篇 MusRec 论文 (arXiv 2511.04376, 2025-11)，标题为 \"Zero-Shot Text-to-Music Editing via Rectified Flow and Diffusion Transformers\" — 与 FlowSonic 高度重合。这引发了严重的自我抄袭/增量工作疑虑。需要核实 MusRec 的具体内容。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "cd6c43cd-df88-46fb-966a-d257b80299b3", "uuid": "375a3a29-8abd-4ac4-bb05-d2c8a8fb8bb7"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784616900740", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-8b67de4e82cf9e55", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2511.04376\" -o /tmp/musrec.html 2>&1; python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('/tmp/musrec.html') as f:\n    h = f.read()\nm = re.search(r'<blockquote class=\\\"abstract.*?\\\">(.*?)</blockquote>', h, re.S)\nif m:\n    t = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', m.group(1))\n    print('MUSREC ABSTRACT:')\n    print(t.strip()[:3000])\nelse:\n    print('no abstract found')\n\"", "description": "Get MusRec abstract"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "cd6c43cd-df88-46fb-966a-d257b80299b3", "uuid": "145b0548-d020-4d7c-9e48-68fcea75cf47"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8b67de4e82cf9e55", "type": "tool_result", "content": "MUSREC ABSTRACT:\nAbstract: Music editing has emerged as an important and practical area of artificial intelligence, with applications ranging from video game and film music production to personalizing existing tracks according to user preferences. However, existing models face significant limitations, such as being restricted to editing synthesized music generated by their own models, requiring highly precise prompts, or necessitating task-specific retraining, thus lacking true zero-shot capability. leveraging recent advances in rectified flow and diffusion transformers, we introduce MusRec, a zero-shot text-to-music editing model capable of performing diverse editing tasks on real-world music efficiently and effectively. Experimental results demonstrate that our approach outperforms existing methods in preserving musical content, structural consistency, and editing fidelity, establishing a strong foundation for controllable music editing in real-world scenarios.", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "cd6c43cd-df88-46fb-966a-d257b80299b3", "uuid": "7af88399-2768-4756-9dfd-e69f9910ae60", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T06:55:06.899Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "MUSREC ABSTRACT:\nAbstract: Music editing has emerged as an important and practical area of artificial intelligence, with applications ranging from video game and film music production to personalizing existing tracks according to user preferences. However, existing models face significant limitations, such as being restricted to editing synthesized music generated by their own models, requiring highly precise prompts, or necessitating task-specific retraining, thus lacking true zero-shot capability. leveraging recent advances in rectified flow and diffusion transformers, we introduce MusRec, a zero-shot text-to-music editing model capable of performing diverse editing tasks on real-world music efficiently and effectively. Experimental results demonstrate that our approach outperforms existing methods in preserving musical content, structural consistency, and editing fidelity, establishing a strong foundation for controllable music editing in real-world scenarios.", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
